pageTitle: JFK Medical Center Muhlenberg Harold B. and Dorothy A. Snyder Schools of Nursing, Medical Imaging and Therapeutic Sciences
textBeforeTable: All tracks lead to a Diploma in Nursing from Muhlenberg and an Associate in Science(A.S.) degree from Union County College. New Time Limits for Transferring in Science Courses • Anatomy and Physiology I and II (Biology 105 and Biology 106) must be successfully completed within (5) years prior to enrollment in Muhlenberg School of Nursing. • Microbiology (Biology 108) must be successfully completed within (5) years prior to enrollment in Muhlenberg School of Nursing. • Chemistry (Chemistry 105 or Chemistry 113 and Chemistry 114) remains at the (10) year limit.
